  {"id":"g10-l2-reading-003","grade":10,"lesson":2,"lessonTitle":"Wonders of Creation","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"The Night Sky Club\n\nEvery Tuesday evening, a group of students meets on their school's rooftop to look at the night sky. They use a powerful telescope that the school bought last year. Their teacher, Mr. Karimi, shows them different planets and stars. Last week, they saw Saturn's rings clearly for the first time. Some students said it was the most exciting moment of the year. The club also keeps a notebook where they write down what they see each night. Soon, they hope to visit a real observatory outside the city.","prompt":"What did they see last week?","options":["the Moon","a comet","Saturn's rings"],"answer":"Saturn's rings","difficulty":"medium"},
