  {"id":"g10-l2-reading-005","grade":10,"lesson":2,"lessonTitle":"Wonders of Creation","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"The Night Sky Club\n\nEvery Tuesday evening, a group of students meets on their school's rooftop to look at the night sky. They use a powerful telescope that the school bought last year. Their teacher, Mr. Karimi, shows them different planets and stars. Last week, they saw Saturn's rings clearly for the first time. Some students said it was the most exciting moment of the year. The club also keeps a notebook where they write down what they see each night. Soon, they hope to visit a real observatory outside the city.","prompt":"What do they hope to do soon?","options":["build a rocket","visit a real observatory","buy a new telescope"],"answer":"visit a real observatory","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l2-reading-006","grade":10,"lesson":2,"lessonTitle":"Wonders of Creation","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"Amazing Blood\n\nBlood is one of the most important parts of our body. It travels through our whole body and never stops moving. Most of blood is a yellow liquid called plasma. Inside plasma, there are red cells and white cells. Red cells carry oxygen to every part of the body, and white cells fight germs and keep us healthy. A healthy adult has about five liters of blood. Doctors say that donating blood is a simple way to help save someone else's life.","prompt":"What color is plasma?","options":["white","yellow","red"],"answer":"yellow","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l2-reading-007","grade":10,"lesson":2,"lessonTitle":"Wonders of Creation","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"tf","style":"konkur","passage":"Amazing Blood\n\nBlood is one of the most important parts of our body. It travels through our whole body and never stops moving. Most of blood is a yellow liquid called plasma. Inside plasma, there are red cells and white cells. Red cells carry oxygen to every part of the body, and white cells fight germs and keep us healthy. A healthy adult has about five liters of blood. Doctors say that donating blood is a simple way to help save someone else's life.","prompt":"White cells carry oxygen around the body.","options":["True","False"],"answer":"False","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l2-reading-008","grade":10,"lesson":2,"lessonTitle":"Wonders of Creation","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"Amazing Blood\n\nBlood is one of the most important parts of our body. It travels through our whole body and never stops moving. Most of blood is a yellow liquid called plasma. Inside plasma, there are red cells and white cells. Red cells carry oxygen to every part of the body, and white cells fight germs and keep us healthy. A healthy adult has about five liters of blood. Doctors say that donating blood is a simple way to help save someone else's life.","prompt":"How much blood does a healthy adult have?","options":["about fifty liters","about five milliliters","about five liters"],"answer":"about five liters","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l2-reading-009","grade":10,"lesson":2,"lessonTitle":"Wonders of Creation","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"tf","style":"konkur","passage":"Amazing Blood\n\nBlood is one of the most important parts of our body. It travels through our whole body and never stops moving. Most of blood is a yellow liquid called plasma. Inside plasma, there are red cells and white cells. Red cells carry oxygen to every part of the body, and white cells fight germs and keep us healthy. A healthy adult has about five liters of blood. Doctors say that donating blood is a simple way to help save someone else's life.","prompt":"Donating blood cannot help other people.","options":["True","False"],"answer":"False","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l2-reading-010","grade":10,"lesson":2,"lessonTitle":"Wonders of Creation","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"Amazing Blood\n\nBlood is one of the most important parts of our body. It travels through our whole body and never stops moving. Most of blood is a yellow liquid called plasma. Inside plasma, there are red cells and white cells. Red cells carry oxygen to every part of the body, and white cells fight germs and keep us healthy. A healthy adult has about five liters of blood. Doctors say that donating blood is a simple way to help save someone else's life.","prompt":"What do white cells do?","options":["fight germs","pump the heart","carry oxygen"],"answer":"fight germs","difficulty":"medium"},
